
Summary:

  php-svn-fetcher is a useful tool to fetch the svn commit log and store logs to mysql database.
  When you get the data, you can do anything you want.
  
Install:
  please rename cronjob/svn-fetcher-sample.ini to svn-fetcher.ini and update the configuration.
  
Requirement:

  Install svn, pdo, pdo-mysql from PECL before you running this script.

Cronjob Example:

  */10 9-18 * * *    /usr/bin/php svn-fetcher.php 

